Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.53,0:00:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,afternoon, Dr. Hawkins. Yes. Tomorrow's Father's Day. Uh-oh. And your spiritual children are out\Nthere. Oh. I want to give you a card. Oh, thank you. And I wanted to thank you for the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.13,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and my question is dealing with avoidance of evil. Early you were talking about dealing with what?\NThe avoidance of dealing with evil, correct? In the past, in the past 7th, 8th, and 9th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.24,0:01:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,10th century, Islam had been very successful in achieving high science, math, architecture,\Nand astronomy, as I perceive it. And for the last thousand years, it's kind of nothing's really
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.80,0:01:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,happened. Yes, it had its high period, yeah. And my question for you is dealing with the perception\Nof what do you feel is the real reason that Islam has slipped? Is it their influence and power or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.46,0:01:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,not achieving their high ideals in these areas?\NI really don't know. It's, you see, don't forget it's factional. It's factional. Islam is factional.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.87,0:01:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like the Catholics and the Protestants in Europe, you know, medieval Europe. Where are all\Nthese little covers come from? And it's factional. Also, Islam is political. People like to think of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:02:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it as a religion. It's a political religion. It's very political. It states there is the house of\NIslam and there is the house of Islam. And there is the house of Islam. And there is the house of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.13,0:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,war. The house of Islam is us and the house of war is everyone else. So, it's very egocentric to a degree, yeah.\NIs there dissatisfaction in Islam because of their lack of influence in the world as it once was today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.76,0:02:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. You're asking me a lot of political questions. My, you know, the principle of hegemony, hegemony.\NWho's the name of my writing? Hawkins? Oh, yeah. I can't handle all these covers. I don't know. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know. I don't know.\NI can't handle all these covers like this. There is the, I view it as primitive. Hegemony, hegemony is part of animal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.48,0:03:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to be the dominant alpha wolf. You don't see religions acting any different than a wolf pack.\NThis is my hill. I'm the dominant one. And this other wolf pack wants to come in. And so we will kill them and drive them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that different?\NNo different. So it's the dominance of the animal ego to dominate, to be king of the hill, to be the alpha male.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.83,0:03:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's unimpressive from a spiritual viewpoint and why the Sufis calibrate so much higher.\NBecause the Sufis transcend all that, you know, lower side of human nature really, see? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:04:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person wants to be an Islamic, I tell them become a Sufi and avoid all that politicalization.\NHello, Dr. Hawkins. I don't really have a question. I just wanted to express my gratitude to you and Susan and ask for a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.86,0:04:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Yes.\NI'm asking for your blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.14,0:04:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Oh, I thought you were asking me a question.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.14,0:04:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God bless you, my love.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.45,0:04:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Be passionate for God. That's what...\NDr. Hawkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.07,0:04:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NQuestion. When we contemplate and meditate, at least for the earlier students, right now when I contemplate,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.26,0:05:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the I which is witnessing the silence is still the I, the ego. It doesn't seem to be I, the awareness.\NHow do you go from I being the ego to I, the awareness when you are contemplating?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.65,0:05:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. From self with a small S to self with a big S.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Yeah. It isn't so much what you do as what you let go of. As you let go of the self with a small S as being a reality, an intrinsic reality, what you do is you surrender the small self to the large self.\NAnd all spiritual endeavor is really aligned with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.49,0:05:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThe realization of the presence of God within is the consequence of removing anything that would be in its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.13,0:06:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, the small self is dissolved into the greater self.\NSo we let go identification with the ego, which presumes that it is the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.48,0:06:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They just sign it right there.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the spiritual techniques are devised to do that.\NPrayer, supplications, karma yoga, selfless service.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.10,0:06:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, be helpful to life without looking for any payback.\NYou see a little beetle on his back flying with his feet in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you put him on his feet.\NYou see a hungry kitten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You put some food out for it.\NYou see a dog that's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes dogs will bark.\NThere's one that barks near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll go out and I'll say, you really don't have to bark.\NYou're not all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And he stops barking.\NHe's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants some kind of contact with some other being.\NAnd I discovered that just going out, even if I tell him you're being a bad dog, please stop barking, he'll stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because all he wants is that sort of human companionship.\NIf I say to him, if you don't stop, I'm going to call the police, he'll stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.30,0:07:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I say to him, if you stop barking, I'm going to call the police, he stops barking.\NSo he wants that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.38,0:07:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat dog wants to hear a human voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.76,0:07:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the folks tie him out and go to town, you know, and leave him.\NAnd pretty soon, woof, woof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.76,0:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Woof, I'm lonely.\NSo I read it that he's lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And no matter what I say to him, he stops woofing.\NYou can do that psychically.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do that psychically.\NPicture yourself leaving your body and going as a lovingness to the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And saying, sweetheart, I love you.\NAnd hugging the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.33,0:08:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And seeing that he's lonely.\NAnd the dog will stop barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.33,0:08:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can actually leave the body and go to the dog.\NAnd the dog's spirit will get a warm, okay feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.39,0:08:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NCan you bless me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.06,0:08:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.73,0:08:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can send your spirit to the dog.\NSay, oh, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're adorable.\NYou're such a sweet dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog will stop barking.\NI want to thank you first for your dedication to us as a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.34,0:08:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And wanted to ask you if you would please chant one om with me.\NShouldn't you do the om?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.63,0:08:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.\NYou want to do an om today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.63,0:08:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NEverybody wants to do an om.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.46,0:09:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Om.\NMy voice is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it go?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Got you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, dog.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today you spoke about the declaration to God.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.18,0:10:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please talk more about that?\NIt takes one sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.55,0:10:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To be the second.\NMake up a sentence that covers what your intention is and how you align your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.82,0:10:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then make that as a formal declaration to God.\NWe do that at the start of every lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.46,0:10:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Glory be to thee, O Lord, most high.\NYou're acknowledging Almighty God as the most high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.30,0:10:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All power and glory be to thee, O Lord.\NMost high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.81,0:10:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NSo by acknowledging divinity, you're already making a declaration that you acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.34,0:10:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,their divinity.\NKrishna says, those who commit to me become mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.44,0:11:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The Psalms say, those who call upon me are mine.\NSo take advantage of that truth and you belong to God once you acknowledge that he is your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.64,0:11:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NKrishna says, those who call upon me are mine and are divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So take advantage of that truth and you belong to God once you acknowledge that he is your\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're acknowledging divinity as your God and you're telling us to are mine and are\Ndear to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Which psalm is it, 29, 19 or is it 19?\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It says the same thing.\NThose who rest their head upon me are mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat's transformative to make that declaration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.90,0:11:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you my memory is something.\N29th Psalm or 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy question is how can one transcend what still appears to be a duality of God imminent
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and transcendent?\NThat's not a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,God knows what God knows.\NHe knows that God knows what He knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that God knows what He knows.\NHe knows that God knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows what He knows.\NWhen you're worshiping God, you know that all the things that Он knows are the same
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.60,0:12:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How can one transcend what still appears to be a duality of God eminent and transcendent?\NYeah, that's not a duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.53,0:12:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a nominalization, just semantic, just semantic.\NIt's a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.72,0:12:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,God transcendent is the traditional God of religion.\NThe transcendent God is elsewhere in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.82,0:12:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's back there before he threw the billiard ball that became the earth.\NAnd he's up there in heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's depicted as the ceiling of the Sistine Chapel.\NGod reaching down to man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:13:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See, he's up there.\NNow, if you go by Genesis, God appeared, created the world, and then apparently disappeared in the interim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.93,0:13:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So God was, and even if he is, he's up there.\NSo that makes you feel separated from God, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're down here and he's up there.\NCreated the universe and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Left you rolling out there all on your lonesome.\NThat which is infinite is always.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Has no beginning, has no end, has no location.\NThe realization I had in the snowbank, and we'll confirm the truth of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.72,0:13:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to confirm it.\NThat which I am existed before all worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.77,0:14:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That which I am will still be after all worlds have disappeared.\NIt's just out of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.73,0:14:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity arises out of the Godhead, arises divinity as creator.\NAnd first there is the Godhead, out of which arises God as creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.01,0:14:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And God's creation manifests as the universe.\NBut each one is a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NGodness arises out of the Godhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.87,0:14:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NI am struggling with trying to stay aware of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.85,0:14:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the busyness of my day.\NI may start out in the morning making a commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then by the end of the day, I see that I wasn't even aware of God all day.\NWell, you weren't thinking about God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness is one thing.\NThinking about is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.58,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness is present or you wouldn't be complaining that you'd stop thinking about God.\NSo don't confuse thinking about God with awareness of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of awareness of God, you're distressed that you, you know, stop thinking about God.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.28,0:15:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there are some people who think about God all the time, but it doesn't do much good.\NAnd then there's other people who only think of God rarely, but it seems to do them a lot of good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you make your declaration for the day in the morning.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.97,0:15:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your declaration for your life and your declaration for the day.\NAnd you ask God for forgiveness that you can't function within the world and mentally keep repeating his name all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that if you're in an ashram.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.29,0:16:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.13,0:16:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to thank you for being a teacher and all you've done and all you are doing for us.\NSo just thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.55,0:16:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.91,0:16:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOh, he brought a bowling ball with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.70,0:16:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Down the alley.\NDr. Hawkins, I wish to extend my love and gratitude to yourself and Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, would you be willing to muscle test if I am dual or multiple personality?\NWe'll ask permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission.\NAsk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You suspect it could be a factor based on the occurrence yesterday, possibly recontextualizing.\NWell, he's talking about different levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:17:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't really have two personalities.\NYou know, he is not a compartmentalized personality, because you wouldn't be complaining about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they usually do not suspect it.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.74,0:17:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Tragedy.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,People who worry about it, they don't have it.\NWhat they really mean is different moods, different states of consciousness, but not different personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.22,0:17:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has their upside and their downside, you know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.84,0:17:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.47,0:18:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWe kid around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.10,0:18:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If time is an illusion,\Nhow come there is a progression from birth to childhood to adulthood to old age?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.46,0:18:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're, you're conjecturing something called time in which this occurs.\NIt would occur without the conjecture of time and see this go into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.40,0:18:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need time to explain that to you.\NWhere'd you come up with time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.78,0:18:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a superimposition and you're saying this is happening in time.\NIt's sort of like a track at the bottom of a TV program.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.28,0:18:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.40,0:18:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call that track that I've done at the bottom?\NUh, time gets imprinted on, it gets imprinted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not innate to experience.\NAnd if you let go resisting the experience of time, it disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.52,0:19:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of time, which is subliminal all the time.\NIf you become conscious of it and let go resisting it, what will happen is you'll disappear time, which is sometimes handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.27,0:19:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to drive.\NI'm Phoenix to Sedona and it takes place experientially in, uh, less than a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.82,0:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You just leave Phoenix and you're in Sedona and there's no memory of, uh, you know, uh, time progression.\NIn fact, that's one of the fastest ways to transcend the ego is to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.92,0:19:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go of time.\NTime imprinting and let go resisting this, the experience of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.16,0:19:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you let go resisting it, it will eventually all of a sudden disappear and then you're in timelessness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.03,0:19:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you constantly have to ask people, you know, what time, how much time we got left here and would the body then stop aging?\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:20:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The body goes on by itself, but he doesn't eat by time.\NIt eats when he thinks it needs to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.38,0:20:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can let go needing to eat too, you know, and then somebody has to remind you, you better eat.\NThere's always somebody nuisancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling you it's time to eat all the time.\NI said, I ate Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.46,0:20:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the hell I want to eat now.\NIt's only Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.36,0:20:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they complain you're too skinny.\NYou know, you can't keep them happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You, your work and research has really changed our lives.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.94,0:20:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NTime is a fast track to transcending the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:21:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.34,0:21:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is a super imposition, which is projected on to phenomenal.\NIt is not intrinsic to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.24,0:21:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness.\NThere are people who live in different time dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are different cultures in which time is experienced differently.\NI told you when I was in Ecuador, there was two planes out a week from, uh, there were two, two planes a week out of Ecuador, Wednesday and Saturday or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.42,0:21:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got there for the Wednesday plane.\NThey said the Wednesday plane was leaving till Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And in Ecuador, 10,000.\N10,000 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:22:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It just didn't make a darn bit of difference that happened in Chicago.\NI would have been all of a sudden, but in Ecuador, they sort of live beyond time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.55,0:22:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, I told you before in the middle of the airport in Ecuador, yeah, is a clock, which stopped many years ago.\NNobody bothered to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.60,0:22:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wednesday plane is not leaving till Saturday.\NI said, okay, Saturday went back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.48,0:22:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was there at quarter 12.\NPlane was going to leave at 12 and all of a sudden there was one plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.22,0:22:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One, one airplane on the whole, in the whole airport.\NAnd, uh, all of a sudden this engine shut down, uh, because it was siesta time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.26,0:22:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They shut the engines down on this plane from 12 till three o'clock at three o'clock.\NBrrng, the siesta time was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.24,0:22:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The engines started up.\NI got aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We took off.\NDidn't have a slight, didn't feel the slightest stress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.91,0:22:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just okay.\NSomehow in the never, never landed at 10,000 feet in Ecuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.00,0:22:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI heard that on your video.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.51,0:23:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.\NIt's wonderful to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.19,0:23:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact, yeah.\NLive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.25,0:23:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No distress.\NWonderful to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI came here to thank you with my respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.44,0:23:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a fact.\NYou just sort of transcend time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.41,0:23:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So no matter what happens, just pretend you're in Ecuador.\NTime doesn't make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved Ecuador for that reason.\NIt was like never, never land.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.91,0:23:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I can remember my question.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.31,0:23:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been, um, I've been in a happy place for quite a few years and suddenly I come\Nup upon retiring from my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.02,0:24:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been in a happy place for years?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.68,0:24:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it.\NShe's retired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.13,0:24:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, retired.\NI thought you meant a psychically happy place.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.37,0:24:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.94,0:24:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so this retirement seems to be bringing on, and I'm thinking it might be my animal\Nfear of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.22,0:24:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NAnd I identified with that, and I got in a very bad place from my perspective, and I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.30,0:24:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,just.\NYou mean like health worries, financial worries, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.30,0:24:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Financial worries.\NFinancial worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.30,0:24:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOh, you just get to be poor, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.34,0:24:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.\NAnd, and what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.34,0:24:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NWhat's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.34,0:24:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NWell, then you live like a poor person lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.34,0:24:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NNo spending money.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.34,0:24:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NI didn't spend any money for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.43,0:24:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you go find another job.\NThat's what you can do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.43,0:24:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd all those things are part of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.43,0:24:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.62,0:25:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All those things were kind of, um, not in my awareness.\NI was just aware of all of the negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.70,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the what?\NNegatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.79,0:25:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you were writing these negative scenarios.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.71,0:25:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.\NWhat you do is you surrender all these negative scenarios.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.95,0:25:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYou, uh, are homeless, you live on a park bench, you cover yourself up with newspapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.38,0:25:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,let it be okay.\NAnd when you're hungry, you go to the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They always have tea and cookies there.\NThen you, uh, borrow the Wall Street Journal from the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.49,0:25:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go out in the park and read the Wall Street Journal and eat your cookies and coffee\Nfrom the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.61,0:25:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd then you hang out with the bag ladies and, uh, jolly them up and see how they make
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.27,0:25:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a living.\NSo pretty soon you get a basket yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.57,0:25:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAwesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.90,0:25:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, see how free a bag lady is.\NShe doesn't have to be to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.21,0:25:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't have to pay any taxes.\NI mean, it's pretty simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.21,0:25:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.21,0:26:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't have to pay any taxes.\NI mean, it's a pretty great life in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.56,0:26:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in the park.\NMosquitoes are bad, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.69,0:26:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mosquitoes are bad.\NI'm glad to have, um, come out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.81,0:26:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just did not understand why I should go there.\NIt just didn't make any sense for me to...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.81,0:26:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, your mind...\NI know all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.09,0:26:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind will come up with common sense, uh, ways to provide for your needs, you know.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.09,0:26:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How old are you?\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.09,0:26:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.09,0:26:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.09,0:26:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.09,0:26:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.09,0:26:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.09,0:26:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NSixty-three.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.09,0:26:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty-three.\NWell, two years to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.09,0:26:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixty...\NWell, that old Social Security rules, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.70,0:26:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can sign up for Social Security early.\NDid you sign up for it early?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.70,0:26:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I may.\NOh, you signed up for it early.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.89,0:26:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NBecause you don't live long, maybe, to...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.30,0:26:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You might as well use it up while you're living, you know.\NVery true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.30,0:26:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be poor next year.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.30,0:26:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.30,0:26:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.30,0:26:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.30,0:26:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.30,0:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.30,0:26:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.42,0:26:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.42,0:27:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.42,0:27:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, now, you can be poor when you're 95 and you've run out or somethin'.\NYeah, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.58,0:27:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole episode was rather silly as I look on it now, but when I was in\Nit, it felt horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.30,0:27:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in it, it was fearful because fear propagates fear, you know.\NSurvival fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.08,0:27:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the ultimate is to let go one's survival fear and to let one's survival be\Nup to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.84,0:27:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBecause the inevitable is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.84,0:27:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's the difference, when it's an hour later?\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.48,0:27:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't really make that much difference\Nunless it's only how you look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.58,0:27:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,oh isn't that awful\Nbut in the reality is it doesn't make any difference
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.10,0:27:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nthank you very much
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.64,0:27:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's constantly surrendering\Nthe fears as they come up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.41,0:27:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendering the fears as they come up\NI'll be poor and I'll be homeless and then what
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.27,0:28:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I'll die\Nif you're on your way to dying
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.89,0:28:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you need a picture for\NI want to give it to my husband
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.15,0:28:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,oh\Ndemand ID at heaven's door
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.91,0:28:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so security card\Npicture ID
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.69,0:28:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.69,0:28:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,picture ID\Npicture ID isn't that funny
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.50,0:28:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well they probably do demand picture ID\Nhello
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.56,0:28:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,how do they know they got the right person\Nthank you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.92,0:28:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a question\Nbut I just wanted to say thank you thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.62,0:28:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nfor your work and your dedication to God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.50,0:28:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you\Nyes and thank you for thanking me
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.50,0:28:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\Nit's inspiring and I'm very grateful
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.62,0:28:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,alright honey\NGod bless you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.37,0:29:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you\Nyes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.46,0:29:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,here we have Kleenex\Ngive you a slight charge
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Kleenex surcharge\Nyes go ahead speak
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.29,0:29:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just\Nhad an experience literally
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.29,0:29:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the day that I was coming out here to see you\Nwhere I discovered that somebody I was in a relationship with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.99,0:29:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,completely betrayed me\Nand lied to me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,like contrived lies\Nlike my intuition had been screaming at me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.79,0:29:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I confronted this person\Nlike
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.59,0:29:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's distressing me is like\Nhow
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.13,0:29:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,like the why of the\Nlike the attraction of that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.58,0:29:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,like how I brought that into my life\Nand I'm like
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.89,0:29:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,oh yeah karma\Nit's called karma
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.89,0:30:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah it's called karma\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,each life is a marine with karma\Nyeah stop weeping and listen to me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.30,0:30:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,stop the crying now and just listen to me\Nand so this person betrayed you yes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.75,0:30:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Ntherefore you have to forgive the one in you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.75,0:30:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,who has betrayed others\Nwhat comes at you is always what is already within you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.07,0:30:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore\Nyou pray to God for forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.07,0:30:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for the one in you\Nwho unwittingly
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.07,0:30:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or not being conscious like you are now\Nbetrayed others
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.07,0:30:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the only way to heal it\Nyou have to own that within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.94,0:30:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask for forgiveness\Nand forgive the one in you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.94,0:30:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,who betrayed others in other lifetimes\Nbecause it didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.94,0:30:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn't know better\Nhe didn't know whatever it was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.45,0:31:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how you heal it\Nand disconnect yourself from the karma coherence of the collective
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.45,0:31:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Nforgive the one in you who betrayed others
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.49,0:31:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,if it weren't for that one\Nyou wouldn't have brought this negative karma
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.49,0:31:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this is why\Nthis is a realm
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.67,0:31:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the undoing of negative and the gaining of positive\Nso you forgive the one
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.67,0:31:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask God for forgiveness\Nfor the one in you who betrays others
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.67,0:31:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,how many could live\Nyou know many a lifetime
